1 SECTION 1.(b) There is appropriated to the Office of State Budget and
2 Management the sum of four million six hundred fifty thousand one hundred seventy-six dollars
3 ($4,650,176) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide the following
4 directed grants:
5 (1) Five hundred fifty thousand dollars ($550,000) to Halifax County to be
6 allocated as follows:
7 a. Three hundred fifty thousand dollars ($350,000) for a new ambulance.
8 b. Two hundred thousand dollars ($200,000) for 18 self-contained
9 breathing apparatus for the Darlington Volunteer Fire Department.
10 (2) Seven hundred thousand dollars ($700,000) to Halifax Fire and Rescue, Inc.,
11 to purchase a fire truck.
12 (3) One hundred fifty thousand dollars ($150,000) to the Town of Enfield to upfit
13 fitness building and purchase apparatus for the Fire Department.
14 (4) Fifteen thousand one hundred seventy-six dollars ($15,176) to the Town of
15 Scotland Neck to purchase body cameras and other needed equipment for the
16 Police Department.
17 (5) Two million two hundred ten thousand dollars ($2,210,000) to the Town of
18 Roanoke Rapids for needs of its fire department, including a new ladder truck,
19 generator, and air packs.
20 (6) One million twenty-five thousand dollars ($1,025,000) to the Town of Weldon
21 to be allocated as follows:
22 a. Eight hundred fifty thousand dollars ($850,000) for a new fire engine.
23 b. One hundred seventy-five thousand dollars ($175,000) for building
24 renovation and site preparation and a viper radio system purchase.
25
26 PART II. NORTHAMPTON COUNTY PUBLIC PROJECTS
27 SECTION 2.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
28 Budget and Management the sum of thirteen million fifty thousand dollars ($13,050,000) in
29 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide directed grants to the following
30 entities:
31 (1) Four hundred thousand dollars ($400,000) to the Town of Rich Square for
32 wastewater treatment improvements.
33 (2) Seven million dollars ($7,000,000) to the Town of Garysburg for water system
34 improvements.
35 (3) Two million one hundred fifty thousand dollars ($2,150,000) to the Town of
36 Seaboard to be allocated as follows:
37 a. Five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) for Community Center
38 renovation.
39 b. One million two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($1,250,000) for street
40 replacement and repairs.
41 c. Four hundred thousand dollars ($400,000) for renovation of the Old
42 Seaboard Bank.
43 (4) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) to the Town of Woodland for the
44 construction of a new town hall.
45 (5) One million five hundred thousand dollars ($1,500,000) to Northampton
46 County for wastewater treatment expansion.
47 SECTION 2.(b) There is appropriated to the Office of State Budget and
48 Management the sum of four million seven hundred fifty-six thousand dollars ($4,756,000) in
49 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide the following directed grants:
50 (1) Six thousand dollars ($6,000) to the Town of Conway Police Department for
51 video conferencing equipment.
