13 PART III. WARREN COUNTY PUBLIC PROJECTS
14 SECTION 3.(a) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
15 Budget and Management the sum of thirty-six million forty-two thousand five hundred thirty
16 dollars ($36,042,530) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide directed
17 grants to the following entities:
18 (1) Eighteen million two hundred ninety-two thousand five hundred thirty dollars
19 ($18,292,530) to Warren County to be allocated as follows:
20 a. Five million four hundred thirty thousand five hundred dollars
21 ($5,430,500) for a regional water system water tank.
22 b. Six million sixty-four thousand one hundred dollars ($6,064,100) for
23 extension of Eaton's Ferry Sewer.
24 c. Four million eight hundred three thousand three hundred dollars
25 ($4,803,300) for the Soul City force main replacement.
26 d. Nine hundred ninety-four thousand six hundred thirty dollars
27 ($994,630) for the Soul City Boulevard watermain replacement.
28 e. One million dollars ($1,000,000) for a waterline extension at the
29 Industrial Site in Soul City.
30 (2) Seventeen million seven hundred fifty thousand dollars ($17,750,000) to the
31 Town of Warrenton to be allocated as follows:
32 a. Ten million dollars ($10,000,000) for wastewater treatment plant
33 rehabilitation.
34 b. Three million seven hundred fifty thousand dollars ($3,750,000) for
35 sewer system rehabilitation.
36 c. Four million dollars ($4,000,000) for water system rehabilitation.
37 SECTION 3.(b) There is appropriated to the Office of State Budget and
38 Management the sum of nine million six hundred six thousand nine hundred twenty dollars
39 ($9,606,920) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide the following
40 directed grants:
41 (1) Five million two hundred seventy-seven thousand dollars ($5,277,000) to
42 Warren County to be allocated as follows:
43 a. One million eight hundred thousand dollars ($1,800,000) for the needs
44 of the Churchill-Five Forks Fire Department, including replacement
45 of fire engines, brush truck, rescue boat, and fire radios and purchase
46 of self-contained breathing apparatus equipment, rescue boat upgrade
47 or replacement, and mobile fire radio replacement.
48 b. One hundred seventy-five thousand dollars ($175,000) to purchase a
49 brush truck for the Inez Volunteer Fire Department.
